Now I have comprehensive information about the sp-slider component. Let me compile the findings into a complete response with working code examples.

## sp-slider Component in Adobe UXP

The `sp-slider` is a built-in Spectrum component available in UXP since version 4.1. No imports or external libraries are needed - it works out of the box.

### Basic Usage

```html
<!-- Simple slider -->
<sp-slider min="0" max="100" value="50"></sp-slider>

<!-- Slider with label -->
<sp-slider min="0" max="100" value="50">
  <sp-label slot="label">Volume</sp-label>
</sp-slider>

<!-- Disabled slider -->
<sp-slider min="0" max="100" value="50" disabled></sp-slider>
```

### Available Attributes

| Attribute | Type | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `min` | number | 0 | Minimum value |
| `max` | number | 100 | Maximum value |
| `value` | number | midpoint | Current value |
| `step` | number | 1 | Increment step (e.g., `step="0.01"` for decimals) |
| `disabled` | boolean | false | Disables the slider |
| `variant` | string | - | Visual style: `"filled"`, `"tick"`, `"ramp"` |
| `fill-offset` | string | - | For filled variant: `"left"` or `"right"` |
| `tick-step` | number | - | Spacing between tick marks |
| `tick-labels` | boolean | - | Show labels on tick marks |

### Variant Examples

```html
<!-- Filled variant (fills from left to current value) -->
<sp-slider min="0" max="100" value="50" variant="filled">
  <sp-label slot="label">Brightness</sp-label>
</sp-slider>

<!-- Filled with offset -->
<sp-slider min="0" max="100" value="50" variant="filled" fill-offset="left">
  <sp-label slot="label">Balance</sp-label>
</sp-slider>

<!-- Tick variant with labels -->
<sp-slider min="0" max="100" value="50" variant="tick" tick-step="20" tick-labels>
  <sp-label slot="label">Quality</sp-label>
</sp-slider>

<!-- Ramp variant (width increases toward max) -->
<sp-slider min="0" max="100" value="50" variant="ramp">
  <sp-label slot="label">Intensity</sp-label>
</sp-slider>

<!-- Decimal precision -->
<sp-slider min="0" max="1" value="0.5" step="0.01" variant="filled">
  <sp-label slot="label">Opacity</sp-label>
</sp-slider>
```

### Event Handling (JavaScript)

```javascript
// Change event - fires on mouse release (final value)
document.querySelector("#mySlider").addEventListener("change", (event) => {
    const value = event.target.value;
    console.log("Final value:", value);
});

// Input event - fires while dragging (real-time updates)
document.querySelector("#mySlider").addEventListener("input", (event) => {
    const value = event.target.value;
    console.log("Current value:", value);
    // Update preview or display
    document.querySelector("#valueDisplay").textContent = value;
});
```

### Complete Working Example for UXP Plugin

```html
<!-- HTML -->
<div class="slider-container">
  <sp-slider id="thresholdSlider" min="-60" max="0" value="-35" step="1" variant="filled">
    <sp-label slot="label">Silence Threshold (dB)</sp-label>
  </sp-slider>
  <span id="thresholdValue">-35 dB</span>
</div>
```

```javascript
// JavaScript
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const slider = document.querySelector('#thresholdSlider');
    const valueDisplay = document.querySelector('#thresholdValue');

    // Real-time update while dragging
    slider.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
        valueDisplay.textContent = `${e.target.value} dB`;
    });

    // Final value when released
    slider.addEventListener('change', (e) => {
        const threshold = parseInt(e.target.value, 10);
        console.log('Threshold set to:', threshold);
        // Call your function here
        detectSilences(threshold);
    });
});
```

### Important Notes

1. **No imports needed** - Spectrum UXP components are available automatically in UXP plugins
2. **Event timing** - The `change` event fires only on mouse release; use `input` for real-time feedback
3. **UXP limitation** - In some Adobe apps, canvas/UI updates may not reflect until mouse release even with `input` event
4. **Premiere Pro** - Works in Premiere Pro 25.6+ with UXP plugin support

### Sources

- [Adobe XD UXP sp-slider Documentation](https://developer.adobe.com/xd/uxp/uxp/reference-spectrum/User%20Interface/sp-slider/)
- [Photoshop UXP sp-slider Documentation](https://adobedocs.github.io/uxp-photoshop/uxp-api/reference-spectrum/Spectrum%20UXP%20Widgets/User%20Interface/sp-slider/)
- [Spectrum Web Components Slider](https://opensource.adobe.com/spectrum-web-components/components/slider/)
- [UXP Slider Change on Move Forum Discussion](https://forums.creativeclouddeveloper.com/t/uxp-slider-change-on-move/2701)
- [Adobe UXP Photoshop Plugin Samples (GitHub)](https://github.com/AdobeDocs/uxp-photoshop-plugin-samples/blob/main/ui-kitchen-sink/index.html)
- [Premiere Pro UXP HTML Events](https://developer.adobe.com/premiere-pro/uxp/resources/recipes/html-events/)

